{"inkVersion":21,"root":[[{"->":"aristotle_intro"},["done",{"#f":5,"#n":"g-0"}],null],"done",{"aristotle_intro":[["^Aristotle: Welcome, traveler, to the Lyceum. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n","^Aristotle: I have spent my life walking the gardens of thought, asking: what is the foundation of knowledge? ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n","^Aristotle: Tell me—do you place your trust in the senses, which reveal the world, or in the mind, which interprets it? ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n",["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.15.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^The senses—observation first, then reason. ","#","^moral:empiricism:+1","/#",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.16.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1","flg":18},{"s":["^Pure reason—the mind shapes reality. ","#","^moral:rationalism:+1","/#",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.15.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev",{"VAR?":"empiricism"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"empiricism","re":true},"/ev","^Aristotle: Indeed! Nothing enters the mind without first passing through the senses. ","#","^speaker:aristotle ","/#","#","^sticker:empiricism_eye","/#","\n","^Aristotle: Yet tell me—are the senses always trustworthy, or do they sometimes mislead us? ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n",[["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-0.26.0.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^They are trustworthy. ","#","^moral:empiricism:+1","/#",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-0.26.1.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1","flg":18},{"s":["^They can deceive us. ","#","^moral:rationalism:+1","/#",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-0.26.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.0.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev",{"VAR?":"empiricism"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"empiricism","re":true},"/ev","^Aristotle: Then you honor the natural sciences, grounding knowledge in what is seen and touched. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n","^Aristotle: You will find truth in the cataloging of plants, the charting of stars, the study of animals. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n",{"->":"story_end"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-0.26.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.1.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev",{"VAR?":"rationalism"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"rationalism","re":true},"/ev","^Aristotle: Ah, then reason must refine what the senses give, as the sculptor refines the marble. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n","^Aristotle: We must weigh appearances carefully, separating truth from illusion. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n",{"->":"story_end"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.16.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev",{"VAR?":"rationalism"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"rationalism","re":true},"/ev","^Aristotle: Then you walk the path of logic and deduction, seeking principles that underlie the chaos of experience. ","#","^speaker:aristotle ","/#","#","^sticker:rationalism_brain","/#","\n","^Aristotle: But tell me, can reason stand without the senses, or must it always be rooted in the world we perceive? ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n",[["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-1.26.0.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0","flg":18},{"s":["^Reason alone is enough. ","#","^moral:rationalism:+1","/#",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-1.26.1.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1","flg":18},{"s":["^Reason must begin from the senses. ","#","^moral:empiricism:+1 ","/#","#","^moral:rationalism:+1","/#",{"->":"$r","var":true},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-1.26.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.0.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev",{"VAR?":"rationalism"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"rationalism","re":true},"/ev","^Aristotle: Then you are like the mathematician, who builds entire worlds from axioms and proofs. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n","^Aristotle: But beware—reason cut off from reality may soar too high, and lose sight of the earth. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n",{"->":"story_end"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"aristotle_intro.0.c-1.26.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.1.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev",{"VAR?":"empiricism"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"empiricism","re":true},"/ev","ev",{"VAR?":"rationalism"},1,"+",{"VAR=":"rationalism","re":true},"/ev","^Aristotle: Ah, the true middle path! The senses provide the raw material, and reason shapes it into knowledge. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n","^Aristotle: Thus does wisdom emerge—not from one alone, but from their union. ","#","^speaker:aristotle","/#","\n",{"->":"story_end"},{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"story_end":["done",{"#f":1}],"global decl":["ev",0,{"VAR=":"rationalism"},0,{"VAR=":"empiricism"},"/ev","end",null],"#f":1}],"listDefs":{}}